
[1]raiment

   RA'IMENT, n. [for arrayment. See Array and Ray.]

   1. Clothing in general; vestments; vesture; garments.

                              Gen. 24. Deut. 8.

   Living, both food and raiment she supplies.

   2. A single garment.

   [In this sense it is rarely used, and indeed is improper.]
